4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROVIDING THAT THE LEGISLATURE MAY ESTABLISH A
5 PROGRAM TO RETURN EXCESS REVENUE TO RESIDENT INCOME TAXPAYERS; PROVIDING THAT
6 THE PROPOSED ACT BE SUBMITTED TO THE QUALIFIED ELECTORS OF MONTANA.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Legislature may refund excess revenue. (1) The legislature may enact
11 a program to provide income tax refunds for resident taxpayers when the state has excess revenue.
12 (2) If enacting income tax refunds for resident taxpayers, the legislature may consider:
13 (a) the amount of revenue that triggers the refunds;
14 (b) how to calculate the refund amount;
15 (c) eligibility requirements for the refund; and
16 (d) how to distribute the refunds.
17
18 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an
19 integral part of Title 15, and the provisions of Title 15 apply to [section 1].
20
21 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Effective date. [This act] is effective on approval by the electorate.
22
23 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Submission to electorate. [This act] shall be submitted to the qualified
24 electors of Montana at the general election to be held in November 2026 by printing on the ballot the full title of
25 [this act] and the following:
26 [] YES on Legislative Referendum ____.
27 [] NO on Legislative Referendum ____.
